 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevieofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evie of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(8/3/01 8:12:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.mr.net/exin/eq/eviesmall.gif border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: anyone got some tips, how a mage win a fight in duel or </span><hr size=1> it all depends on what class you're fighting.  we are great vs melee and totally suck vs enchanter.  I'll just post some of the duels I've had...<br>
<br>
vs warrior and most melee: ds self, ds pet, make sure it's a water pet for backstabs, jboots yourself and kite the melee around.  cast scars of sigil once or twice, but your pet should finish him off.  sks and rangers would probably snare yer pet tho, so make sure you give him daggers of symbols they do help a little.  <br>
<br>
vs rogue: be careful he doesn't bs you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ds self, pet, kite rogue with water pet.  Probably won't even need to cast on him and just let the pet finish him off since rogues don't have as many hp as warrior, and if you stop you might take a BS.<br>
<br>
vs wizard: sic pet on the wizard, he will try to root pet to get the pet off of him.  try using an air pet for this it might interrupt his casting.  when he's casting root on the pet, just nuke him down.  if he doesn't have the good resists, we can nuke a wizard down before they can nuke us down.  <br>
<br>
vs. enchanter: they are mean lil things!  make sure you have a dispell out, he'll mez yer pet and all you gotta do is dispell it.  But they will mana sieve you like crazy so it sucks.  And they rune themselves! what nerve :P  I fought a few enchanters, the only one that got me was one with a pet.  I can't get that pesky thing off of me =(  I can kite it around but I never get to med.  he was lvl 60 tho with nice resists and I was only 56 at the time.  But the other enchanters I just nuke 'em down and they die.  keep your MR high.<br>
<br>
vs. druid: I'm not dumb enough to challenge a druid yet.<br>
<br>
vs. mage: pets on pets, nuke each other I guess.  I'd like to see what the botb was like.  nobody on vazaelle was able to attend cuz the server had just opened. :P  it all depends on the epic too.  <br>
<br>
vs. shaman: the only shaman i dueled I have really no clue as to what he was doing, but basically i nuked him down with my pet beating on him and he died. <br>
<br>
vs. cleric: no real challenge here they're not really a dueling class.  <br>
<br>
vs. necros: again, not dumb enough to challenge them. :P<br>
<br>
but always use your DS when fighting melee.  especially rogues and monks.  they hit fast but they don't hit hard, and a DS just chews through them.  And if you're in the arena, bind there, have gate memmed.  it throws people off.  always use scars of sigil for the fast cast time, and it's rumored that our low level magic DD will interrupt casting.  always have a dispell memmed.  When buffing, have 3 or 4 fakes on top for when you get dispelled, any clickables up top too.  then do phantom armor/elemental armor and then shield of the magi last.  wear the right resist gear - chanters MR, wizzies FR and CR, shammies DR and PR... etc.  <br>
<br>
 <p>[58 Useless] Evie (Nerfed) <<a
href="http://www.invirtue.com">In Virtue</a>>
