Reapply velocity<br>
Anull pet<br>
Reapply velocity<br>
  <br>
<br>
Dispell necro/druid dots immediatedly after they land on you. Easiest way is to keep an open spot at top of buffs and then left click removing it to create space so anull only removes dot and jboots.  Use level 8 shock of blades because it has 2.1 second cast time and knocks people out of casting.  If you chain shock of blades a caster your pet will kill them if they are stupid and dont drag pet out range.<br>
<br>
Against bards, on vallon zek they have this really annoying bug that allows bards to charm your pet and /pet get lost  to make your pet go away.  Most people consider it an exploit but bards do it anyways because they are gay. Not really much you can do in defense other than hit them with a big nuke and use your wand of swords to give them 3 insta right clicks of death. <p>57 Conjurer <Dark Storm>
Vallon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalahadbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KalahadBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(8/4/01 5:00:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: anyone got some tips, how a mage win a fight in duel or </span><hr size=1> The &quot;stand there and nuke them down&quot; thing isn't a very good strategy...dunno who ya were duelin but they obviously were not too smart.  The ONLY class i will not duel is a level 60 shaman because...they are evil and stuffs =(.  Freakin DoT's and torpor suck.  Necro's arn't too tough, (i'm speaking from level 60 tactics here) basicly before the pet starts, i make an epic pet, hit it with see invis, then wait for him to DS, then i burnout him and then valient companion.  Then i dispell the see invis with cancel/nullify magic (not annull since it takes two), Fight starts, banish necro pet...epic pet is now on the necro...necro cannot fear because of the valient companion, and since the top buff spot on the pet is open because of the see invis dispelled, whenever he mezzes pet just dispell it off and the pet will basicly eat the necro alive, throw some nukes in too if you feel like not bein lazy.<br>
<br>
Druids, agian, keep that top spot open on the pet for dispelling snare/root, and give the pet the sow spell (cant think of the name atm since i rarely use it)  Tho snare will cancel it, epic pet has very high resists, especualy with daggers of symbols, so snare will be resisted alot.  Also mala is nice since the stun will actualy hit occasionaly if ya hit them with it.<br>
<br>
Also, against other mages...standing there and nuking each other is the stupidest thing i can think of, outside of standing there and doing nothing.  Any mage at level 60 that doesn't have respectable MR/FR should just retire, i myself have 234 fr and 177 MR self buffed with my normal every day gear on.  In the BOTB my tactic was to char/SoS the pet to death since pets have low resists and are NPCs so spells can hit them for full.  I tested damage of char/shock of steel on me with 200 fr/mr which is about what i had for the botb and they did about 150 damage on average...on the pet char will do 702 95% of the time.  Take 10 char's to kill a respectable mage on average and 4 to kill an earth pet...so i'm at 60% with a pet and the other mage has no pet, ya know, whos gonna win?  Heh but of course i screwed up cause i was on a new keyboard, hit my shielding 4 straight times in the buffing stage and well, started without a pet and almost buffless /shrug.<br>
<br>
But in general, the way you duel each class is something you have to discover for yourself, you have to know what that class can do at that specific level and you have to know what YOU can do with your specific level/gear.  Ohh yah did i mention level 60 shaman suck?  Bleh.  A good level 60 mage with an epic can beat any class in general, a good shaman is the only thing i'm still struggling with but i'll figure it out someday.  Thinkin i'll try banishing the pet, and chain dispelling torpor off the shaman while the pet beats on him....hmm thats a good idea hehe.  The most important thing while dueling casters is to keep the pets top buff spot free so you can dispell any roots or such while keeping burnout on the pet (the haste helps a TON in interrupting casters).  Well thas about it.<br>
